Kenya on Thursday reported 21 new Covid-19 cases and two more deaths, raising the tally of infections to 758 and the death toll to 42. Dr Mercy Mwangangi, Health Chief Administrative Secretary (CAS), said in a briefing that three coronavirus patients left hospitals in the past 24 hours, taking the number of recoveries in the country to 284. All the 21 patients who tested positive are Kenyans and the youngest is seven-years-old, Dr Mwangangi said. Twelve of the new Covid-19 patients are from Mombasa, four from Nairobi, four from Kajiado and one from Uasin Gishu.   The country has 272 confirmed cases of the disease.